This paper focuses on developing a framework for fairness-enhancing interventions in machine learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also emphasizes the importance of incorporating ethics and legal compliance into machine-assisted decision-making, which relates to the sub-category of cyberlaw and cybersecurity (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper discusses the need for data quality and representativeness, which falls under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of best practices in software engineering and machine learning, which relates to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and software engineering (cs.SE).
